1. What is an API?

API (Application Programming Interface) is a way for applications to communicate.

Example:

Your Application → API Request → Server
                              ↓
                       JSON Response
Example API request:

https://api.github.com/users/octocat

Response:

{
 "login": "octocat",
 "id": 1,
 "followers": 5000
}
Types of Web Services
1. REST API

Most common modern API.

Features:

Uses HTTP methods

Returns JSON or XML

Stateless

Example endpoints:

GET /users
POST /users
PUT /users/1
DELETE /users/1
2. SOAP Web Services

Older enterprise protocol.

Features:

Uses XML

Strict standards

Used in banking systems

3. GraphQL

Modern API query language.

Example:

{
 user(id:1) {
  name
  email
 }
}
3️ HTTP Methods:===
Method	Purpose
GET	Retrieve data
POST	Create data
PUT	Update data
DELETE	Remove data

Example:

GET https://api.example.com/users
4️ Working with APIs in Python:==

Most common library: requests

Install:

pip install requests
5️Example: GET Request:===
import requests

url = "https://api.github.com/users/octocat"

response = requests.get(url)

data = response.json()

print(data["login"])
print(data["followers"])

Output example:

octocat
5000
6️ Example: POST Request:--

Send data to API.

import requests

url = "https://jsonplaceholder.typicode.com/posts"

data = {
    "title": "DevOps",
    "body": "Learning APIs",
    "userId": 1
}

response = requests.post(url, json=data)

print(response.json())
7️ Example: API with Headers:---

Many APIs require authentication headers.

Example:

headers = {
 "Authorization": "Bearer YOUR_TOKEN"
}

response = requests.get(url, headers=headers)
8️ Example: API with Query Parameters:---
params = {
 "q": "python",
 "page": 1
}

response = requests.get(url, params=params)

Request becomes:

https://api.example.com/search?q=python&page=1
9️JSON Data Handling:----

Most APIs return JSON.

Example:

data = response.json()

print(data)

Example JSON:

{
 "name": "Vineetha",
 "role": "DevOps Engineer"
}

Access values:

print(data["name"])
10. Error Handling:----

Always check status codes.

Code	Meaning
200	Success
201	Created
400	Bad request
401	Unauthorized
404	Not found
500	Server error

Example:

if response.status_code == 200:
    print("Success")
else:
    print("Error:", response.status_code)
 Real DevOps API Examples

APIs commonly used in DevOps:

GitHub API

Get repositories, commits, pipelines.

Example:

https://api.github.com/users/{username}/repos
AWS APIs

Manage cloud services programmatically.

Example operations:

Create EC2

List S3 buckets

Start instances

Kubernetes API

Control cluster resources.

Example:

GET /api/v1/pods
